# Cloudflare Pages headers for the deployed demo (assembled into site/ by
# deploy-pages.yml). Cloudflare already serves .wasm as application/wasm; the
# Content-Type here is belt-and-suspenders for WebAssembly.instantiateStreaming.
# The wasm is NOT content-hashed (wasm-bindgen --out-name emits a stable
# bdinfo_rs_wasm_bg.wasm), so it must REVALIDATE: a long immutable cache would pin
# a redeploy's fresh glue against a year-stale wasm (the .js glue revalidates but
# the wasm would not). No COOP/COEP: the scan is single-threaded FileReaderSync in
# a Worker, not SharedArrayBuffer, so cross-origin isolation is neither needed nor
# wanted (it would break cross-origin loads for no benefit).
/*.wasm
  Content-Type: application/wasm
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
